04/05/2010
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Interior Minister Gordana Jankulovska insisted on Monday (May 3rd) that police control the security situation and there is no reason for concern after a statement by the National Liberation Army (NLA).
At the weekend, the group claimed responsibility for a shootout near the border with Kosovo, after police discovered a large stash of weapons in the area.
Jankulovska assured the public that police are on top of security issues in the region.
In other news, Jankulovska said that the investigation into the death of President Boris Trajkovski remains open, and her ministry continues to collect evidence and new information that could shed light on the case.
Trajkovski died on February 26th 2004 in a plane crash in Bosnia and Herzegovina.
(Alsat, A1, Makfax, MIA - 03/05/10)
